Blue Wild Angel: Live at the Isle of Wight is a posthumous live
album by Jimi Hendrix released on November 12, 2002, and
re-released in 2004 as a 3-disc 'Deluxe Sound & Vision Edition
in a special box and slip cover format as part of Experience
Hendrix's plan to re-release most of Jimi Hendrix's recorded
material. The album documents Hendrix's last U.K. live performance
at the Isle of Wight Festival on August 31, 1970, barely three
weeks before his death. Some songs on the album were available
on the 1971 release Isle of Wight.
